# Force LF line endings for all text files, in the repo and in the working tree.
#
# Why this exists: the editorial build scripts (scripts/gen-compiled.mjs,
# gen-prerender.mjs, gen-seo-artifacts.mjs) emit their artifacts with LF. The
# repo has core.autocrlf=true, so before this file existed a Windows checkout
# rewrote those same generated files to CRLF on disk. The build's
# line-ending-sensitive guards (npm --prefix scripts run check) then reported
# every generated file as "stale" even when its content was correct, and
# git status showed permanent CRLF churn that masked real diffs.
#
# `eol=lf` pins LF on checkout regardless of autocrlf, so the working tree
# matches what the generators write and `check` can pass on any platform.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: never normalize line endings or attempt to diff/merge them.
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.png   binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.webp  binary
*.avif  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
*.eot   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.mp4   binary
*.webm  binary
